Biodiversity

Biodiversity refers to the variety of life on Earth at all its levels, from genes to ecosystems.

Key Components:

  • Species diversity
  • Genetic diversity
  • Ecosystem diversity

Importance of Biodiversity:

  • Maintains ecosystem balance and resilience
  • Provides resources for food, medicine, and industry
  • Supports ecosystem services like pollination and water purification
  • Has cultural and aesthetic value

Biodiversity loss is a critical environmental issue, driven by factors such as habitat destruction, climate change, pollution, and overexploitation of resources.

); } export default Biodiversity;
